# 🌌 How AURA Works Now — Full Architecture

## The Big Picture

```mermaid
graph LR
    A["📱 AURA Mobile App\n(Flutter)"] -->|WebSocket| B["⚡ FastAPI Backend\n(Port 7860)"]
    B -->|HTTP JSON API| C["🔍 SearXNG\n(Port 8888)"]
    B -->|Groq API| D["🧠 Llama 3.3 70B\n(Cloud LLM)"]
    B -->|Embeddings| E["💾 ChromaDB\n(Vector Memory)"]
    C -->|Aggregates| F["Google\nBing\nDDG\nWikipedia\n+ 70 more"]
```

---

## Step-by-Step: What Happens When You Send a Message

### 1️⃣ User Types a Message in AURA Mobile
```
"What's the latest IPL score today?"
```
The Flutter app sends this via **WebSocket** to your FastAPI backend.

### 2️⃣ Backend Decides: Does This Need Live Search?

[main.py](file:///d:/ANTIGRAVITY/llm%20APP/python_backend/main.py#L165-L172) checks for trigger keywords:

```python
keywords = ["score", "ipl", "news", "today", "weather", "match", 
            "latest", "cricket", "who is", "what is", "how is", 
            "price", "stock", "search"]
```

| Message | Triggers Search? |
|---|---|
| "What's the IPL score?" | ✅ Yes (`score`, `ipl`) |
| "Explain quantum physics" | ❌ No (pure LLM) |
| "Latest news on AI" | ✅ Yes (`latest`, `news`) |
| "Hello, how are you?" | ❌ No |

### 3️⃣ If Search Triggered → SearXNG Pipeline

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant B as FastAPI Backend
    participant S as SearXNG (localhost:8888)
    participant E as Google/Bing/DDG/etc.
    
    B->>S: GET /search?q=IPL+score&format=json&categories=general
    S->>E: Fan-out to 70+ engines simultaneously
    E-->>S: Aggregated results (deduplicated)
    S-->>B: JSON response with titles, URLs, snippets, engine source
    Note over B: Formats into "LIVE RESEARCH DATA" context
```

The [search_agent.py](file:///d:/ANTIGRAVITY/llm%20APP/python_backend/agent_plugins/search_agent.py) sends a simple HTTP GET:

```
GET http://127.0.0.1:8888/search?q=IPL+score+today&format=json&categories=general&language=en
```

SearXNG returns:
```json
{
  "results": [
    {
      "title": "IPL 2026 Live Score - CSK vs MI",
      "url": "https://example.com/ipl-live",
      "content": "Chennai Super Kings 185/4 after 18 overs...",
      "engine": "google"
    }
  ]
}
```

> [!TIP]
> **Fallback:** If `general` returns nothing, it automatically retries with `categories=news` and `time_range=day` for real-time events.

### 4️⃣ Memory Context (ChromaDB)

Simultaneously, [NeuralMemory](file:///d:/ANTIGRAVITY/llm%20APP/python_backend/main.py#L78-L111) searches your local vector database for relevant past conversations:

```
User asked about IPL before → retrieves past context
```

### 5️⃣ Everything Gets Combined → Sent to Llama 3.3

The backend builds a single prompt:

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ SYSTEM: You are AURA. Be natural. Context:  │
│                                             │
│ [Memory Context from ChromaDB]              │
│                                             │
│ LIVE RESEARCH DATA:                         │
│ Source: IPL 2026 Live Score - CSK vs MI      │
│ URL: https://example.com/ipl-live           │
│ Engine: google                              │
│ Snippet: Chennai Super Kings 185/4...       │
│                                             │
│ [Chat History]                              │
│                                             │
│ USER: What's the latest IPL score today?    │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

This is sent to **Groq's Llama 3.3 70B** via streaming API.

### 6️⃣ Streamed Back to Mobile

Each token from Llama streams back via WebSocket:

```
Backend → {"type": "chunk", "content": "The"} → Mobile
Backend → {"type": "chunk", "content": " latest"} → Mobile
Backend → {"type": "chunk", "content": " IPL"} → Mobile
...
Backend → {"done": true} → Mobile
```

The Flutter app renders each chunk in real-time with the neural typing animation.

---

## The Two Search Modes

### Mode 1: Chat Search (Automatic)
Happens inside the `/chat` WebSocket — triggered by keywords in your message.

```mermaid
graph TD
    A["User sends message"] --> B{"Contains keywords?"}
    B -->|Yes| C["SearXNG search"]
    B -->|No| D["Skip to LLM"]
    C --> E["Inject results as context"]
    E --> F["Send to Llama 3.3"]
    D --> F
    F --> G["Stream response to mobile"]
```

### Mode 2: Research Hub (Dedicated)
The `/research` WebSocket endpoint — a full research pipeline with **3 phases**:

| Phase | What Happens | What User Sees |
|---|---|---|
| 🔍 **Scan** | SearXNG searches with category routing | "Scanning Neural Web..." |
| 🧪 **Synthesize** | Llama 3.3 writes a research report from results | Streaming markdown report |
| 🔗 **Correlate** | Builds topic correlation map | Visual correlation chart |

Category routing in the Research Hub:
```
"GitHub" → search_query += " site:github.com"    (general category)
"Academic" → search_query += " research papers"   (science category)  
"News" → news category with time_range=day
```

---

## What You Need Running

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph "Your Machine"
        A["🔍 SearXNG\nPort 8888\n(Start first)"]
        B["⚡ FastAPI\nPort 7860\n(Start second)"]
    end
    subgraph "Cloud"
        C["🧠 Groq API\n(Llama 3.3)"]
    end
    subgraph "Mobile"
        D["📱 AURA App"]
    end
    
    B --> A
    B --> C
    D --> B
```

| Service | Command | Port |
|---|---|---|
| **SearXNG** | `cd searxng-master && python -m searx.webapp` | 8888 |
| **AURA Backend** | `cd python_backend && uvicorn main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 7860` | 7860 |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Start SearXNG first**, then the AURA backend. If SearXNG isn't running when a search-triggering message comes in, AURA will return: *"No live data clusters found. Ensure SearXNG is running."*

---

## Before vs After

| Aspect | ❌ Before (Tavily + DDG) | ✅ Now (SearXNG) |
|---|---|---|
| **Cost** | Tavily paid API | Free, self-hosted |
| **Rate Limits** | DDG blocks after ~20 requests | Zero limits |
| **API Keys** | Needed `TAVILY_API_KEY` | No API key needed |
| **Search Sources** | Tavily (1 engine) or DDG (1 engine) | 70+ engines simultaneously |
| **Privacy** | Data sent to Tavily servers | Everything stays local |
| **Reliability** | DDG 403 blocks were common | Self-hosted = always available |
| **Result Quality** | Good (single source) | Excellent (aggregated + deduplicated) |
| **Dependencies** | `tavily-python`, `duckduckgo-search` | Only `requests` (already installed) |
